Interface IElement

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAttribute, IClass, IClassifier, IInterface, IOperation, IPackage, IParameter, IRelationAttribute

    public interface IElement
    UML Element. This class is parent of almost all uml interfaces.
    Author:
    Jose Carreno

        IElement getOwner()

      • getFullyQualifiedName

        String getFullyQualifiedName(String separator)
        Calculates element's path, i.e.: it's name prefixed by a separated list of its parents name, ordered from the root to the leaf. (e.g. : separator = '.' => org.test.core.MyClass, or separator = '/' => org/test/core/MyClass
        Parameters:
        separator - used to separate names inside the path
        Returns:
        element's path

      • getStereotypes

        Set<IStereotype> getStereotypes()
        Lists element's stereotypes.
        Returns:
        List of stereotypes, can be empty but never null.

      • getVisibility

        Visibility getVisibility()
        Gets element's visibility
        Returns:
        visibility. It must never be null.

      • hasStereotype

        boolean hasStereotype(String stereotype)
        Checks whether the element has this stereotype, identifier by its name. This is case sensitive, i.e. : "Boundary" <> "boundary" <> "BOUNDARY" are considered as 3 distinct sterotypes.
        Parameters:
        stereotype - stereotype name.
        Returns:
        true if this element has this stereotype.

      • getModifier

        String getModifier()
        Element's modifier. This is a free to use string that should be used to give more details about the type. In java, modifier can be used to give more information about collections and generics for type safety.
        Returns:
        element's modifier.
